Dear Friends, 
 
On Thursday, February 11 at 6:30 PM, I’m hosting a telephone town hall on COVID-19 relief. Included on the call will be representatives from Atlanta Legal Aid to discuss housing and your rights as a renter. We’ll also have someone from the IRS to discuss stimulus checks, folks from the SBA to discuss PPP and EIDL loans and Emory to share information about COVID-19 and vaccines.
 
￼
  
We will discuss:
 
	•	Unemployment, stimulus checks, vaccinations, PPP and EIDL loans;
	•	Evictions, foreclosures and your rights as a renter;
	•	Vaccines and COVID-19 health issues and more; 
	•	The event will take place on your phone, but will also be streamed live on my Facebook page @RepHankJohnson and website: hankjohnson.house.gov/live.
 
Please join us Thursday, Feb. 11 at 6:30 PM.  
 
WHO:    
 
	•	Congressman Hank Johnson (GA-04); 
	•	Terri Denison: Georgia District Director of the U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA); 
	•	Ruby Riesinger: Area Director and a Business Consultant for the University of Georgia Small Business Development Center in DeKalb and Rockdale; 
	•	Linda Berkman: IRS Congressional Liaison; 
	•	Attorney Karen Brown: Atlanta Legal Aid; 
	•	Nancy Flake Johnson: Urban League of Atlanta; 
	•	Dr. Zanthia Wiley: Emory’s Division of Infectious Diseases and Director of Antimicrobial Stewardship;
 
WHAT:          Telephone town hall on COVID-19 relief;   
  
WHEN:          Thursday, February 11 at 6:30 PM; 
 
WHERE:         To register: https://hankjohnson.house.gov/live or listen on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/RepHankJohnson.
 
